  &lt;p id="66SMfr"&gt;The Apple Watch often sees its fair share of limited-time discounts throughout the year, but &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/24191617/amazon-prime-day-tech-deals-guide-2024"&gt;Amazon’s Prime Day&lt;/a&gt; offers a chance for someone to shop deals across most available models all at once.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="c-float-left c-float-hang"&gt;&lt;aside id="lrQEpx"&gt;&lt;div data-anthem-component="readmore" data-anthem-component-data='{"stories":[{"title":"The Verge’s guide to Amazon Prime Day 2024","url":"https://www.theverge.com/24191617/amazon-prime-day-tech-deals-guide-2024"},{"title":"The best Amazon Prime Day deals you can get","url":"https://www.theverge.com/e/23962008"}]}'&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/aside&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p id="yoIJUA"&gt;For this Prime Day, we’re seeing some worthwhile sales across the range of the &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/23369207/apple-watch-se-2022-review-smartwatch"&gt;2022 Apple Watch SE&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/23878981/apple-watch-series-9-ultra-2-review-double-tap-precision-finding-siri"&gt;Apple Watch Series 9&lt;/a&gt;, and even the pricey &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/23878981/apple-watch-series-9-ultra-2-review-double-tap-precision-finding-siri"&gt;Apple Watch Ultra 2&lt;/a&gt;. Most of these require an Amazon Prime subscription, but Amazon’s excellent &lt;a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CHX9M3BM/?tag=theverge02-20" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;$100 discount on the Ultra 2&lt;/a&gt; does not.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="64PLpL"&gt;While most Apple Watches are pretty similar at their core (iOS notifications on your wrist, fitness tracking, health metrics, etc.), it’s the extra features added or omitted from some models that often determine which is right for you — as well as your budget, of course....&lt;/p&gt;
